{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/halitosis/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"5db4c662-1e04-59fa-a241-2374b9a15c3d","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 2fd9a166-79bf-4bbc-a232-a7f201895047 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 2fd9a166-79bf-4bbc-a232-a7f201895047 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 72d9b3a3-1c42-4a64-8219-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 719bae14-62e1-4561-9c35-a7f201895047 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 719bae14-62e1-4561-9c35-a7f201895047 --><!-- begin field ee03f5b1-2a48-4dc8-8fb4-a7f201895047 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field ee03f5b1-2a48-4dc8-8fb4-a7f201895047 --><!-- begin field 823deec1-d700-4755-8dea-a7f201895047 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 823deec1-d700-4755-8dea-a7f201895047 --><!-- begin field 94c20d20-52d1-48b4-9fbd-a7f201895047 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 94c20d20-52d1-48b4-9fbd-a7f201895047 --><!-- begin field fdd0de4f-8f22-4295-bf26-a7f201895047 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field fdd0de4f-8f22-4295-bf26-a7f201895047 --><!-- begin field a4253cc2-682f-4d88-bb0b-a7f201895047 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field a4253cc2-682f-4d88-bb0b-a7f201895047 --><!-- end item 72d9b3a3-1c42-4a64-8219-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"ea95b9d4-34a7-5d1a-82a8-55bfdd82196e","topicId":"fe0b6e92-2668-4612-aca4-2a9b60ac4f39","topicName":"Halitosis","slug":"halitosis","lastRevised":"Last revised in September 2019","chapters":[{"id":"fbb800d8-0a88-595c-b899-0a65190b8e58","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"fd2b97bd-db6b-55cc-b4e2-35124cffec66","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"6bd01b8c-56bc-586d-aff5-f44fdb32ee60","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"78fa51ef-a4b8-5018-b7e3-42049eace7f4","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"5cdbf49b-e67d-54e2-b879-dcd54d37cb53","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"81ff3380-c70b-5c69-9e8a-461ac2bc4554","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"b414cfd5-0732-59ba-ba20-d7d239b332c4","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"e512b3a8-808c-5329-8940-83d75972d158","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"604b5628-660e-569a-8f50-d379558771c4","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":